This paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of disentangled representations is a key aspect of the proposed approach, which is a popular area of research in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses user studies and perceptual distance metrics, which are common evaluation methods in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
